%body
  / Header
  .intro-header
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-12
          .intro-message
            %h1 Make thousands badges
            %h1 for your event
            %h3 by using the one mockup and list of participants.
            %hr.intro-divider
              %ul.list-inline.intro-social-buttons
                %li
                  %a.btn.btn-default.btn-lg{:href => "#go"}
                    %i.fa.fa-fw
                    %span.network-name How it work?
    / /.container
  / /.intro-header
  / Page Content
  %a{name: "go"}
  .content-section-b.go
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-5.col-lg-offset-1.col-sm-push-6.col-sm-6
          %hr.section-heading-spacer
            .clearfix
            %h2.section-heading
              Usually designers edit one mockup of badges by changing few fields and save it lots of time.
            %p.lead
              But now they shouldn't do it.
        .col-lg-5.col-sm-pull-6.col-sm-6
          %img.img-responsive{:alt => "", :src => "assets/baddd.png"}
  .content-section-a
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-5.col-sm-6
          %hr.section-heading-spacer
            .clearfix
            %h2.section-heading
              Upload the mockup of badge
              <br>in SVG format
            %p.lead
              After that upload the list of your participants in csv format.
              We will support other formats of input files in the nearest future.
            %p.lead
              %b Note:
              you can download prepared
              %a{:href => "csv_example.csv"} CSV
              and
              %a{:href => "badge.svg"} SVG
              files if you don't want to draw them.
        .col-lg-5.col-lg-offset-2.col-sm-6
          %img.img-responsive{:alt => "", :src => "assets/ipad.png"}
    / /.container
  / /.content-section-a
  .content-section-b
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-5.col-lg-offset-1.col-sm-push-6.col-sm-6
          %hr.section-heading-spacer
            .clearfix
            %h2.section-heading
              Check the fields that must
              %br be at the badge
            %p.lead
              and press the button 'Generate'. Wait some minutes for processing your csv-file and generating a single images.
              We take the fields about your participants and put them to single images automatically.
        .col-lg-5.col-sm-pull-6.col-sm-6
          %hr.section-heading-spacer
            .clearfix
            %h2.section-heading
              Well done!
    / /.container
  / /.content-section-b
  .content-section-a
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-5.col-sm-6
          %hr.section-heading-spacer
            .clearfix
            %h2.section-heading
              Yay! Now you can download your badges in a zip-archive.
            %p.lead
              We created this service at RailsRumble 2014 for 2 days and hope that our prototype will be useful for you.
    / /.container
  / /.content-section-a
  .banner
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-6
          %h2 Let's get started!
        .col-lg-6
          %ul.list-inline.banner-social-buttons
            %li
              %a.btn.btn-default.btn-lg{:href => new_order_path}
                %i.fa.fa-twitter.fa-fw
                %span.network-name Go to make badges
    / /.container
  / /.banner
  / Footer
  %footer
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-12
          %ul.list-inline
            %li
              %a{:href => "#"} Home
          %p.copyright.text-muted.small Was made at RailsRumble 2014.
